Sure, here are some example sentences in Serbian that use the word "mrtvo" in different forms and positions:

1. *Mrtvo* drvo je palo na put. (A dead tree fell onto the road.)
2. Videla sam *mrtvog* miša u kuhinji. (I saw a dead mouse in the kitchen.)
3. Ona je *mrtva* umorna od posla. (She is dead tired from work.)
4. *Mrtvom* čoveku ne možeš pomoći. (You can't help a dead person.)
5. Njegov izraz lica je bio *mrtav* ozbiljan. (His facial expression was dead serious.)
6. Zvukovi iz sobe su bili *mrtvi* tihi. (The sounds from the room were dead silent.)
7. Da li si siguran da ovo neće ubiti *mrtvu* pticu? (Are you sure this won't kill a dead bird?)
8. *Mrtva* priroda je omiljeni motiv slikara. (Still life is a favorite motif of painters.)
9. Njihov projekat je *mrtva* trka. (Their project is a dead race.)
10. *Mrtvo* more je poznato po svojoj visokoj saliniteti. (The Dead Sea is known for its high salinity.)

I hope these examples help!